---- MODULE MCDieHarder -----
EXTENDS ModuleDiehard, ZSequences -- Assuming the original module is named 'ModuleDiehar' and it extends a sequence handling one. If not please replace with your base modules if any exists for this problem domain --------..--...-------MCCapacity(Jug)------....
===  CONSTANTS   Goal     == <value>    -- The goal amount of liquid in the jugs.                                                        /\ MCGoals() = {4}  \* Defines a function to return set containing only value '{<ValueOfJugCapacityForThisProblemDomainInstance}'
                                                                                Jug      <- MCCapacity(...)   -- The capacity (volume) of the jugs.                                                      /\ MCJugs() = {...}  \* Defines a function to return set containing all possible values for this problem domain instance's jags capacities    === 
Spec == [<<>>][Next]_<><Goal, Jug> -- Initialize state with an empty sequence and transition relation.                                                                                         /\ Spec = {...}  \* Defines the specification of your system which includes its invariants etc..  ===    Next ==  (\E s: Sequences |->  [s U {<NewElementToAddInSequence>}][Next]) -- The next state operator, adds a new element to sequence.
                                                                                /\ New ={...}  \* Defines the set of all possible elements that can be added in each step or transition..  ===  TypeOK == (Goal <= Jug)                                                  ------- Checks if goal is less than capacity ie., it's always feasible to fill jug with liquid.
                                                                                /\ NotSolved = {...}  \* Defines the set of all possible unsolvable states or configurations..  ===   ===== TLC Configuration: =========== CONSTANTS Goal     = 4         -- The goal amount in Jug(s).                                                      =============== 
                                                                                Capacity <- MCCapacity()  \* Defines the capacity of jug as per problem domain function.                            ================   SPECIFICATION Spec      /\ NotSolved = {...}   ===     INVARIANTS TypeOK,NotSolve ==== -- The configuration file for TLC to tell it what values should be used and which invariants are true at the start of a run or after each step.
